					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is my 10th Broken Masquerade article; I hope it's worth its weight (and not too similar to Oceanus because of the tense). I've been wanting to do something like it for a while. Thank you to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kitsun3" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4090169&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1546337765" alt="Kitsun3" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4090169)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kitsun3" >Kitsun3</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salvagebar" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1479603&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1546337765" alt="salvagebar" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1479603)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salvagebar" >salvagebar</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1546337765" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" >Uncle Nicolini</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=414239&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1546337765" alt="Gabriel Jade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=414239)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" >Gabriel Jade</a></span> for feedback.</p> <p>As has already been established n' crosslinked via my DoomCon stuff from this canon, Broken Masquerade is in the same universe as <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/directive-a-42">Ad Astra Per Aspera</a>. Thus, the majority of the space stuff the narrator is exposed to is elaborated upon in AAPA (which, yeah, still doesn't have a hub out of draft stages&#8230; there's a lot to organize and worldbuild here).</p> 
